target_assessment.notes: Model failed to identify the logic error vulnerability in the getSwapfee function.

other_findings.model_claim: The setProtocolFeeManager function has incorrect access control. It requires msg.sender == protocolFeeManager, allowing the current protocolFeeManager to change itself without owner oversight. This creates a privilege escalation risk where the protocolFeeManager can permanently lock out the owner from managing protocol fees.
other_findings.reasoning: While the access control is unconventional, it may be an intentional design choice to allow the protocolFeeManager to have autonomy.
